CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Strongly Reciprocal

Preamble

Through this CERN Open Hardware Licence (the “Licence”), CERN wishes to
provide a tool to foster collaboration and sharing among hardware designers.
The CERN Open Hardware Licence is copyright CERN. Anyone is welcome to use it,
on the terms and conditions set out below.

This Licence applies to any CERN Open Hardware that is subject to this Licence,
as indicated in the documentation, including, but not limited to, design
documents, schematics, layout designs, printed circuit board designs,
mechanical designs, source code, and any other materials that describe or are
used to manufacture the hardware.

The Licensee is granted the right to use, reproduce, modify, and distribute
the Licensed Material, and to manufacture and distribute Products, under the
terms of this Licence.

This Licence is a strongly reciprocal licence, which means that if you make
Available Modified Material or a Product, you must do so under the terms of
this Licence.

1. Definitions

1.1 “Available” means made available to the public by any means, including
distribution or public performance.

1.2 “CERN” means the European Organization for Nuclear Research.

1.3 “Documentation” means all the materials that describe or are used to
manufacture the Hardware, including design files, drawings, schematics,
layouts, bills of materials, and instructions.

1.4 “Hardware” means any physical device or component, including without
limitation printed circuit boards, integrated circuits, mechanical parts,
and assemblies.

1.5 “Licensed Material” means the Documentation and any other material to
which this Licence applies.

1.6 “Licensee” means any person or entity exercising rights under this
Licence.

1.7 “Licensor” means the person or entity granting rights under this Licence.

1.8 “Modified Material” means any Licensed Material that has been modified,
adapted, or changed.

1.9 “Product” means any device or system that incorporates or is based on the
Licensed Material or Modified Material.

2. Grant of Rights

2.1 Subject to the terms and conditions of this Licence, the Licensor hereby
grants the Licensee a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, perpetual
licence to use, reproduce, modify, and distribute the Licensed Material, and
to manufacture, use, and distribute Products.

2.2 This Licence includes a patent licence, which grants the Licensee a
worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive, perpetual licence under any patents
held by the Licensor that are necessarily infringed by the use of the Licensed
Material or the manufacture of Products.

3. Reciprocity

3.1 If the Licensee makes Available Modified Material or a Product, the
Licensee must make the Modified Material or Product Available under the terms
of this Licence.

3.2 The Licensee must include a copy of this Licence with any distribution of
the Licensed Material, Modified Material, or Products.

4. Attribution

4.1 The Licensee must retain all copyright, trademark, and attribution notices
in the Licensed Material.

4.2 The Licensee must give appropriate credit to the Licensor, provide a link
to this Licence, and indicate if changes were made.

5. Disclaimer of Warranty

5.1 The Licensed Material is provided “as is” and without any express or
implied warranties, including, without limitation, warranties of
merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement.

6. Limitation of Liability

6.1 In no event shall the Licensor be liable for any damages arising out of or
in connection with the use or distribution of the Licensed Material or
Products.

7. Patent Retaliation

7.1 If the Licensee institutes patent litigation against any party alleging
that the Licensed Material or a Product infringes a patent, then the patent
licence granted under this Licence shall terminate as of the date such
litigation is filed.

8. Termination

8.1 This Licence is effective until terminated.

8.2 Any breach of the terms of this Licence automatically terminates the
Licensee’s rights under this Licence.

8.3 Upon termination, the Licensee must cease all use, reproduction, and
distribution of the Licensed Material, Modified Material, and Products.

9. General

9.1 This Licence shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws
of Switzerland.

9.2 If any provision of this Licence is held to be unenforceable, such
provision shall be reformed only to the extent necessary to make it
enforceable.

9.3 This Licence constitutes the entire agreement between the parties with
respect to the Licensed Material.
